At first he ran straight through the wood, brushing against swishing ferns and slipping on reddish lily-of-the valley leaves — and his cap hung at the back of his neck, held only by its elastic, his knees were hot in the woolen stockings already donned for city wear, he cried while running, lisping childish curses when a twig caught him across the forehead — and fi